title: For Sale:  Colt Fitz Detective Special with Archive Letter
postcontent: Double action Colt collectors here is literally a once in a lifetime firearm for your collection. A 1932 Colt Fitzgerald Detective Special with an archive letter verifying its authenticity. Features the bobbed hammer and cutaway trigger guard and the ever so light trigger pull these are so famous for. . These were modified by Colt employee Henry Fitzgerald for conceal and carry. He was at Colt from 1918 until 1944 and was a respected competition pistol shooter and innovator of combat pistol shooting tactics. He also wrote a book entitled shooting in 1930. These were not exactly the safest guns to carry thus very few were modified. Only a handful of these left on the planet. title: For Sale:  (Sale Pending) Like-New Stainless Steel Ruger GP100 (4" Barrel, .38 Special and .38 Special +P ONLY)
postcontent:
Pictured below is a Stainless Steel Ruger GP100 revolver with a four inch barrel, standard factory gp100 sights, and a factory standard black Hogue grip. The oddity of this particular firearm however is that while most GP100s can fire both .38 special and .357 this little gem is specifically for .38 special ONLY. Only two runs of this firearm exist. Earlier serial numbers were part of a cancelled police order that found their way to the civilian market. The newer serial numbers such as this one were made exclusively for a company called Davidson's (galleryofguns.com) and seem to be no longer in production or for sale.

Brand new, these ran for between $500-700 depending on which FFL ordered it for you. This one as you can see was manufactured on March 19, 2013, before it was sent to Davidson's. I purchased it a little over a year ago on August 6, 2014 and have kept it locked up since, entirely unused.

This revolver is in Like-New condition (I don't consider this new as it now has a third party owner). It has never been fired or used outside of the test shot at the factory, the casing of which was included the shipment. There are a couple very minor scuffs on the rubber grip from storage. The original box the revolver came in as well as all of the documents and even advertisements (such as the Manual, Davidson's ad, NRA ad, etc) that came with it, are present. The spent casing from the factory's test shot is present as well. Also included are the original lock and key for the cylinder, and a tiny bronze pin (or punch?) which the purpose of escapes me.

The revolver functions in double action and single action. The trigger can be rather heavy in the former, but in single action it feels like a hair trigger. The balance is impeccable in my opinion. I must stress again, this unique model is for .38 special and .38 special +P ONLY. It CANNOT fire .357 Magnum. However, the frame is exactly the same as the .357 version, the cylinder is the only difference. If you could somehow acquire a .357 gp100 cylinder, they could be switched out as far as I know.

Now, let's talk about what's included in this deal. While I bought the revolver with the intention of using and carrying it, I never did. The ammunition and accessories I bought for it went unused, locked up along with it. Along with the revolver, you will also receive the following:

1x HKS 203M-P Plain Double Speedloader Case, Black, Medium 

2x HKS 586-A Revolver Speedloader for S&W 586, 686, 581, 681/Ruger GP100 

1x Outbags OB-09SC Nylon OWB Belt Gun Holster for Ruger GP100 / SP101, Taurus 65 / 66 / 82 / 689 Magn. / Tracker 4", S&W 66 / 586 / 686, and Most 4" Revolvers

1x 50 round box of 110 Gr. .38 Special Remington HTP (High Terminal Performance) Semi-Jacketed Hollow Point cartridges.

If you wish to request more information or pictures, you may contact me via email or via this site.

Buyer will be required to provide a non-expired ID, Drivers License, or Concealed Carry Permit and sign a bill of sale (both when we meet). I realize this may be inconvenient, but if you've lived in Hampton Roads long, you know this is a high crime area. I'd prefer to have myself covered if this firearm somehow ends up at a crime scene some day as I am the original purchaser.

$450 (Negotiable to an extent) Cash or United States Postal Money order are they only accepted means of payment. I am not interested in trades of any kind.
